    <text id="B0195T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Galloway writes that the information Jackson gave him about how to find his son
                    was not accurate, and he asks for more information if possible.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Thomas">Tho<hi rend="super">s</hi></abbr> P
                        Jackson <abbr expan="Esquire">Esqr</abbr><lb/>Staunton Virginia</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-10-25">October 25<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Wilmington Delaware</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Respected Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have written to my son at Livingston <abbr expan="Alabama">Ala</abbr> but the
                    letter has been returned to me unclaimed On <abbr expan="August">Aug</abbr> 3<hi
                        rend="super">d</hi> you kindly gave me the directions where to write but it
                    seems strange that no such direction found him. I enclose the letter to you and
                    beg you would try and find him for me if not <orig reg="too">to</orig> much
                    trouble.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly<lb/>and respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>Isaac Galloway<lb/>per WBW</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
